The paper deals with the analysis of capacity and optimal constellations for bit-interleaved coded modulation (BICM), which is a topic related to information theory and communication systems (cs.IT, cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the input distributions and alphabets, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI, cs.NI).
